le":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519228.html?thread=25688380#t25688380","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519228.html?thread=25688380#t25688380","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"noybusiness","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://noybusiness.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":25688380,"talkid":100345,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519228.html?thread=25688380#t25688380","upictitle":"noybusiness: DW R/D friendly","article":"Didier Graffet is great! I met him at the 2013 World Fantasy Convention and he did very detailed illustrations by hand in my convention book when he signed it, then replicated them in my mother's convention book in exact detail. He was incredibly nice and patient.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"3 months ago","ctime":"January 30 2017, 23:47:42 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://noybusiness.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"noybusiness","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"noybusiness","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://noybusiness.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"noybusiness","ctime_ts":1485820062,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/123940693/72144472","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519228.html?thread=25689404#t25689404","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519228.html?thread=25689404#t25689404","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519228.html?thread=25689404#t25689404","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"ext_2751600","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"https://www.facebook.com/diydepression","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":25689404,"talkid":100349,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519228.html?thread=25689404#t25689404","upictitle":"Kyle Gideon: pic#123940693","article":"\"edited by GEORGE R.R. FUCKING MARTIN\"<br /><br />When I first heard about you a few years ago I went to the library and thought you were easily one of the most accomplished authors out there. Like, huge sections seemed to be consumed by massive, angry capslocked George R.R. Martins. Turns out, you're just also a prolific editor. It also turns out, however, that the Wild Cards series is really, really good, and really, really underrated. <br /><br />Anyways, small question about your editing process. Basically, I've heard through the grapevine that the writer GRRM is slightly miffed by editors, so does the editor GRRM take a more laissez-faire approach? Also, if the editor GRRM edited the writer GRRM's novel, would the writer GRRM be annoyed with the editor GRRM?  <br />","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"3 months ago","ctime":"January 31 2017, 01:31:45 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"https://www.facebook.com/diydepression","striked":null,"journaltype":"I","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/icons/facebook-16.png?v=29916?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"Kyle Gideon","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":1,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"ext_2751600","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://www.livejournal.com/profile?userid=72144472&t=I","alias":0}],"dname":"Kyle Gideon","ctime_ts":1485826305,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/91237832/7059164","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519228.html?thread=25689660#t25689660","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519228.html?thread=25689660#t25689660","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519228.html?thread=25689660#t25689660","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"grrm","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":25689660,"talkid":100350,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519228.html?thread=25689660#t25689660","above":25689404,"upictitle":"George R.R. Martin: Spain","article":"I am not miffed by editors.<br /><br />And when editing, no, I do not take a laissez faire approach.  Especially not with Wild Cards.  Editing a shared world anthology is the hardest kind there is, since you're not just editing for quality but also for continuity.  All the pieces need to fit together.","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"3 months ago","ctime":"January 31 2017, 02:51:50 UTC","parent":25689404,"massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"grrm","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"grrm","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"dname":"grrm","ctime_ts":1485831110,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519228.html?thread=25690428#t25690428","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519228.html?thread=25690428#t25690428","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519228.html?thread=25690428#t25690428","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"srdrbr","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://srdrbr.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":25690428,"talkid":100353,"etime_ts":"1485855893","thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/519228.html?thread=25690428#t25690428","above":25689660,"upictitle":"srdrbr: pic#0","article":"While we are on the topic of shared universes and your enormous experience/skills as editor, I have to ask a quick question, hoping for an answer.<br /><br />Have you thought about Shared Universe of Ice and Fire, of course after finishing ASOIAF?<br /><br />Some authors I followed recently finished their main book series, and then decided to retreat to the editor role while other people expanded their universe and wrote other storylines in that universe, which are only loosely connected to the main series.<br /><br />You already did a similar thing with The World of Ice and Fire, and you could only loosen the grip in the future, since that could be unrelated stories, unlike TWOIAF, which was a part of the backstory very important to the main series and had to be meticulously crafted to provide additional layer to the main story.<br /><br />That would be so much different from the fan fiction you dislike since you would get money and creative control while your characters probably wouldn't be even used.<br />","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"3 months ago","below":25690684,"ctime":"January 31 2017, 09:43:10 UTC","parent":25689660,"massactions":0,"subject":"Shared Universe","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://srdrbr.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","color":null,"noctxpopup":0,"side_alias":0,"journal":"srdrbr","inline_css":0,"attrs":null,"is_identity":0,"bold":1,"show_userhead":1,"username":"srdrbr","user_alias":"","profile_url":"http://srdrbr.livejournal.com/profile","alias":0}],"etime":"January 31 2017, 09:44:53 UTC","dname":"srdrbr","ctime_ts":1485855790,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"